    <who name="alvanx">alvanx</who>
    <bug_when>2012-07-13 12:40:48 +0300</bug_when>
    <thetext>In Settings -&gt; Configure Bibletime -&gt; Fonts (path is retranslated from German, so no guarantee), it is possible to set a specific font for each of the module languages that are present in your library. This is great for displaying Greek and Hebrew in optimized fonts, probably also for other non-Latin languages. 

But here&apos;s the problem: The preview always displays Gen 1,1-2 in English. This is clearly a usability bug (if minor). Let me explain. Say I want to set a specific font for Greek. I can do that, but the preview doesn&apos;t help me at all: It previews my font in English, with a Latin script, not in Greek, wit a Greek script. Hence, if I really want to know what the font is going to look like, I first have to exit out of the configuration window and load a bible in the language specified.</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
